# Frontend Rules (React + Vite + Tailwind)

## Component Structure
```
ComponentName/
  index.tsx          # Main component export
  ComponentName.tsx  # Component implementation (if complex)
  useComponentName.ts  # Component-specific hook (if needed)
```

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`ChatList.tsx`, `MessageBubble.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useSocket.ts`, `useAuth.ts`)
- Stores: camelCase with `Store` suffix (`authStore.ts`, `chatStore.ts`)
- Services: camelCase with `.service.ts` suffix (`api.service.ts`)
- Types/interfaces: PascalCase, in `src/types/` or co-located

## State Management (Zustand)
- One store per domain: auth, company, chat, ui, folder, bot, search
- Keep stores flat, avoid deep nesting
- Use selectors for derived state
- Actions defined inside store (not external)

## API Calls (React Query + Axios)
- API client in `src/services/api.service.ts` with base URL and JWT interceptor
- React Query hooks wrap API calls with proper cache keys
- Mutations invalidate relevant queries on success
- Loading/error states handled in components

## Styling (Tailwind CSS)
- Use Holio brand colors via custom Tailwind palette (holio-orange, holio-dark, etc.)
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- Use `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Responsive: mobile-first, but primary target is desktop

## Socket.IO
- Single socket service in `src/services/socket.service.ts`
- Connect on auth, disconnect on logout
- Event listeners set up in custom hooks (e.g. `useSocket`)
- Events follow `domain:action` naming pattern

## Forms
- Use controlled components with React state or React Hook Form
- Validate on submit, show inline errors
- Loading state on submit buttons
